<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-29T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-29T18:00:00-05:00" n="497" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d497">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/261</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-29T18:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 29, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>7073. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from War Trade Board]:</p>
                            <p>No. 260. Your 347, Embassy’s 9240, March 27, 6 p.m. <hi rend="italic">Borneo</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Cornelis</hi> were
                                requisitioned without due consideration having been given to their
                                being in Panama Canal. We thought it wiser to release them
                                later.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>